      "full_body_preview": "Leibniz wrote that *nothing happens without a sufficient reason why it should be so and not otherwise.* He meant this metaphysically. I want to use it domestically.\n\nConsider a boring afternoon — not tragic, not frantic, just boring, of the kind that occupies most of a life. By the principle, the boredom must have a sufficient reason. So: what?\n\nThe shallow answer is *nothing interesting happened.* This is a tautology dressed as a reason. *Boring* and *nothing interesting happened* are the same "
